WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.420 --> 00:00:02.670
- Sometimes, making a big decision at work

2
00:00:02.670 --> 00:00:04.530
can feel like you're
answering the final question

3
00:00:04.530 --> 00:00:08.070
on a game show, everyone's
watching and time is running out.

4
00:00:08.070 --> 00:00:09.630
Are you gonna win the big prize,

5
00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:12.240
or are you gonna go home empty-handed?

6
00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:14.730
It's easy to start doubting yourself.

7
00:00:14.730 --> 00:00:17.220
Now, you'd probably feel more
confident making a decision

8
00:00:17.220 --> 00:00:19.290
if you just had more information.

9
00:00:19.290 --> 00:00:21.570
Usually that means doing in-depth research

10
00:00:21.570 --> 00:00:24.180
and pulling together things
like competitor profiles

11
00:00:24.180 --> 00:00:27.030
and consumer trends and industry insights.

12
00:00:27.030 --> 00:00:29.550
But creating just one of
those reports could take days

13
00:00:29.550 --> 00:00:32.640
or weeks, or even months.

14
00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:35.040
Now, this is where AI can be an incredibly

15
00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:36.690
valuable research partner.

16
00:00:36.690 --> 00:00:39.510
It does way more than just
produce a report faster.

17
00:00:39.510 --> 00:00:42.810
It can scour a range of sources,
get to the key takeaways,

18
00:00:42.810 --> 00:00:45.510
and help you deliver a stronger report.

19
00:00:45.510 --> 00:00:47.250
It's a whole new way
of conducting research

20
00:00:47.250 --> 00:00:49.530
and building understanding on a topic.

21
00:00:49.530 --> 00:00:52.680
Now, let's be clear, this doesn't
mean that the fundamentals

22
00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:54.387
of good research are going away.

23
00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:56.850
You still need to verify
all of your information,

24
00:00:56.850 --> 00:00:59.010
and you still need to
build your own arguments.

25
00:00:59.010 --> 00:01:00.840
And when you're faced
with really difficult

26
00:01:00.840 --> 00:01:03.210
or ambiguous challenges,
the ones where there's

27
00:01:03.210 --> 00:01:05.910
really no simple solution,
you still need to consider

28
00:01:05.910 --> 00:01:08.730
all the angles and make
the final decision.

29
00:01:08.730 --> 00:01:11.220
In this course, you'll
learn how you can use AI

30
00:01:11.220 --> 00:01:14.460
to build deeper understanding
in almost any area,

31
00:01:14.460 --> 00:01:16.950
and you'll discover how
to transform uncertainty

32
00:01:16.950 --> 00:01:20.250
into solid, confident recommendations.

33
00:01:20.250 --> 00:01:22.710
First, we'll show you how
to research a complex topic

34
00:01:22.710 --> 00:01:24.630
